{"title_page": "Kings Park, New York", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name            = Kings Park, New York\n|settlement_type          = [[Hamlet (New York)|Hamlet]] and [[census-designated place]]\n|nickname                 = \n|motto                    =\n\n<!-- Maps -->\n|pushpin_map              = New York\n|pushpin_label_position   = bottom<!-- the position of the pushpin label: left, right, top, bottom, none -->\n|pushpin_label            = Kings Park\n|pushpin_map_caption      = Location within the state of New York\n|pushpin_mapsize          =\n|image_map                = Kings-park-map.gif\n|mapsize                  = 250px\n|map_caption              = U.S. Census map\n|image_map1               = \n|mapsize1                 = \n|map_caption1             =\n\n<!-- Location -->\n|subdivision_type         = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n|subdivision_name         = United States\n|subdivision_type1        = [[U.S. state|State]]\n|subdivision_name1        = New York\n|subdivision_type2        = [[List of counties in New York|County]]\n|subdivision_name2        = [[Suffolk County, New York|Suffolk]]\n|government_footnotes     = \n|government_type          = \n|leader_title             = \n|leader_name              = \n|leader_title1            = \n|leader_name1             = \n|established_title        = \n|established_date         =\n\n<!-- Area -->\n|area_footnotes           = \n|area_magnitude           = \n|area_total_km2           = 17.1\n|area_land_km2            = 16.1\n|area_water_km2           = 1.0\n|area_total_sq_mi         = \n|area_land_sq_mi          = \n|area_water_sq_mi         =\n\n<!-- Population -->\n|population_as_of         = [[2010 United States Census|2010]]\n|population_footnotes     = \n|population_total         = 17282\n|population_density_km2   = auto\n|population_density_sq_mi =\n\n<!-- General information -->\n|timezone                 = [[North American Eastern Time Zone|Eastern (EST)]]\n|utc_offset               = -5\n|timezone_DST             = EDT\n|utc_offset_DST           = -4\n|elevation_footnotes      = \n|elevation_m              = 53\n|elevation_ft             = 174\n|coordinates              = {{coord|40|53|19|N|73|14|33|W|region:US_type:city|display=inline,title}}\n|postal_code_type         = [[ZIP code]]\n|postal_code              = 11754\n|area_code                = [[Area code 631|631]]\n|blank_name               = [[Federal Information Processing Standard|FIPS code]]\n|blank_info               = 36-39672\n|blank1_name              = [[Geographic Names Information System|GNIS]] feature ID\n|blank1_info              = 0954667\n|website                  = \n|footnotes                = \n}}\n'''Kings Park''' is a [[Hamlet (New York)|hamlet]] and [[census-designated place]] (CDP) in the [[Administrative divisions of New York#Town|Town]] of [[Smithtown, New York|Smithtown]], [[Suffolk County, New York|Suffolk County]], [[New York (state)|New York]], United States, on [[Long Island]]. The population was 17,282 as of the 2010 census.<ref name=\"Census 2010\">{{Cite web| url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/G001/1600000US3639672| archive-url=https://archive.today/20200212192506/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/G001/1600000US3639672| url-status=dead| archive-date=2020-02-12| title=Geographic Identifiers: 2010 Demographic Profile Data (G001): Kings Park CDP, New York| publisher=U.S. Census Bureau, American Factfinder| accessdate=2013-01-02}}</ref>\nIt is an unincorporated hamlet of [[Smithtown, New York]]\n\nIt is bordered by [[Nissequogue, New York|Nissequogue]] to its east across the [[Nissequogue River]], by [[Fort Salonga, New York|Fort Salonga]] to its west, by [[Commack, New York|Commack]] to its southwest, and by the hamlet of [[Smithtown (CDP), New York|Smithtown]] to its southeast. Kings Park is noted for its schools, numerous parks, and natural environment. Its relative tranquility prompted it to be the site of the [[Kings Park Psychiatric Center]] instead of New York City.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://a-better-place.com/kings-park-new-york-i187189/|title=Kings Park, New York - Kings Park|website=a-better-place.com|language=en|access-date=2019-11-12}}</ref>\n\n==Geography==\nKings Park is located at {{Coord|40|53|19|N|73|14|33|W|type:city}} (40.888497, \u221273.242582).<ref name=\"GR1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/geographies/reference-files/time-series/geo/gazetteer-files.html|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=2011-04-23|date=2011-02-12|title=US Gazetteer files: 2010, 2000, and 1990}}</ref>\n\nAccording to the [[United States Census Bureau]], the CDP has a total area of {{convert|17.1|km2|order=flip}}, of which {{convert|16.1|km2|order=flip}} is land and {{convert|1.0|km2|order=flip}}, or 5.93%, is water.<ref name=\"Census 2010\"/>\n\n==Demographics==\nAs of the [[census]] of 2010, there were 17,282 people and 6,212 households residing in the CDP. The [[population density]] was 2,787.4 per square mile (1,073.4/km\u00b2). There were 6,469 housing units at an average density of 1,043.4/sq&nbsp;mi (401.8/km\u00b2). The racial makeup of the CDP was 80.1% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 5.1% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.1% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 8.4% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.02% [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 4.9% some other race, and 1.3% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 16.3% of the population.<ref name=\"Census 2010 DP\">{{Cite web| url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_SF1/SF1DP1/1600000US3639672| archive-url=https://archive.today/20200212203723/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_SF1/SF1DP1/1600000US3639672| url-status=dead| archive-date=2020-02-12| title=Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics: 2010 Demographic Profile Data (DP-1): Kings Park CDP, New York| publisher=U.S. Census Bureau, American Factfinder| accessdate=2013-01-02}}</ref>\n\nThere were 6,212 households in 2010, out of which 34.6% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 60.2% were headed by [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 9.4% had a female householder with no husband present, and 27.1% were non-families. 23.3% of all households were made up of individuals, and 12.1% were someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.71, and the average family size was 3.24.<ref name=\"Census 2010 DP\"/>\n\nIn the CDP, the population was spread out with 23.3% under the age of 18, 6.6% from 18 to 24, 23.4% from 25 to 44, 29.4% from 45 to 64, and 17.2% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 43.3 years. For every 100 females, there were 93.7 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 90.8 males.<ref name=\"Census 2010 DP\"/>\n\nOver the period 2007-2011, the median annual income for a household in the CDP was $92,921, and the median income for a family was $106,128. Males had a median income of $78,882 versus $55,872 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the CDP was $37,980. About 1.6% of families and 3.3% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 2.6% of those under age 18 and 6.3% of those age 65 or over.<ref>{{Cite web| url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/ACS/11_5YR/DP03/1600000US3639672| archive-url=https://archive.today/20200212085010/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/ACS/11_5YR/DP03/1600000US3639672| url-status=dead| archive-date=2020-02-12| title=Selected Economic Characteristics: 2007-2011 American Community Survey 5-Year Estimates (DP03): Kings Park CDP, New York| publisher=U.S. Census Bureau, American Factfinder| accessdate=2013-01-02}}</ref>\n\nKings Park is largely a Catholic community, with nearly 60% identifying as Catholic. The town parish, St. Joseph\u2019s has the largest census population of all religious communities in the Town of Smithtown. The current pastor is Father Peter J. Dugandzic and has been in service since June 26, 2019.\n\nKings Park is generally considered a reliably [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] hamlet. In the [[2016 United States presidential election|2016 Presidential Election]] President [[Donald Trump]] defeated [[Hillary Clinton]] in the hamlet.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2018/upshot/election-2016-voting-precinct-maps.html,%20https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2018/upshot/election-2016-voting-precinct-maps.html|title=An Extremely Detailed Map of the 2016 Presidential Election|last=Bloch|first=Matthew|date=2018-07-25|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-04-09|last2=Buchanan|first2=Larry|issn=0362-4331|last3=Katz|first3=Josh|last4=Quealy|first4=Kevin}}</ref>\n\n== Landmarks ==\nKings Park is home to Leo P. Ostebo Kings Park Heritage Museum, the only school community managed town heritage [[museum]] in the United States, which is located in the first school building built in 1928.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://kpheritagemuseum.net/about.html|title=Leo P. Ostebo Kings Park Heritage Museum - About|last=Piacentino, Jr.|first=Joseph |website=kpheritagemuseum.net|access-date=2017-05-19}}</ref>\n\n[[Sunken Meadow State Park]] borders [[Long Island Sound]] and is accessible by the [[Sunken Meadow State Parkway]]. It is a part of the New York State Parks system. In addition to the water, the park has {{convert|6|mi|0}} of public trails and 27 holes of golf. The park's facilities are used for different activities, among them various distance running competitions. \"Cardiac Hill\" is well known by local runners.{{citation needed|date=May 2017}}\n\nThe [[Nissequogue River]], {{convert|6|mi|0}} in length, empties into Long Island Sound and is used for different types of water activities.{{citation needed|date=May 2017}} The river flows through the [[Nissequogue River State Park]].\n\nKings Park Bluff, sandwiched between [[Sunken Meadow State Park]] and Short Beach in Smithtown sits the Kings Park Bluff which empties into the Long Island Sound. Used as a boat launch and a popular fishing location for locals.{{citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n\n==Notable people==\nKings Park is the hometown of [[Houston Astros]] catcher/second baseman/outfielder [[Craig Biggio]].{{citation needed|date=April 2020}} Biggio was named one of the five greatest [[second basemen]] of all time by baseball statistician [[Bill James]]. He is also the modern-era record-holder for [[Hit by pitch|HBP]]s with 273, and the first player in history to be named an [[Major League Baseball All-Star Game|All-Star]] at both the catcher and second baseman positions.<ref>{{cite web|title=Craig Biggio Stats|url=http://www.baseball-almanac.com/players/player.php?p=biggicr01|website=Baseball Almanac|accessdate=27 January 2017}}</ref> Biggio was elected into the [[National Baseball Hall of Fame]] in 2015. [[Kings Park High School]] named their men's varsity baseball field after [[Craig Biggio]].\n\nOther notable residents:\n*[[Percy Crosby]], author, comics illustrator, creator of ''[[Skippy (comic strip)|Skippy]]''{{citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n*[[Jim Pavese]], former NHL defenseman{{citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n*[[John Petrucci]], [[John Myung]], and [[Kevin Moore]], founding members of progressive metal band [[Dream Theater]]{{citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n*[[Bobby Goepfert]], professional ice hockey goaltender{{citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Kings Park, New York}}\n\n* [http://www.kingsparkli.com/ Kings Park Chamber of Commerce]\n* [http://www.kpcsd.k12.ny.us/ Kings Park Central School District]\n* [http://www.kpheritagemuseum.net/ Kings Park Heritage Museum]\n* [http://www.kingsparkcivic.com/ Kings Park Civic Association] \n* [http://kppcajourneythroughhistory.webs.com/ Kings Park Psychiatric Center: A Journey Through History], by Jason Medina\n* [http://www.cmarshall.net/miscellaneous/kppc.htm Kings Park Psychiatric Center], by Chris Marshall, including a high-quality PDF map and a photo essay of the abandoned hospital\n* [http://www.mykppcpictures.com/ KPPC History], by Robert Saal: photo collection\n\n{{SmithtownNY}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Smithtown, New York]]\n[[Category:Census-designated places in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Long Island Sound]]\n[[Category:Census-designated places in Suffolk County, New York]]\n[[Category:Populated coastal places in New York (state)]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name            = Kings Park, New York\n|settlement_type          = [[Hamlet (New York)|Hamlet]] and [[census-designated place]]\n|nickname                 = \n|motto                    =\n\n<!-- Maps -->\n|pushpin_map              = New York\n|pushpin_label_position   = bottom<!-- the position of the pushpin label: left, right, top, bottom, none -->\n|pushpin_label            = Kings Park\n|pushpin_map_caption      = Location within the state of New York\n|pushpin_mapsize          =\n|image_map                = Kings-park-map.gif\n|mapsize                  = 250px\n|map_caption              = U.S. Census map\n|image_map1               = \n|mapsize1                 = \n|map_caption1             =\n\n<!-- Location -->\n|subdivision_type         = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n|subdivision_name         = United States\n|subdivision_type1        = [[U.S. state|State]]\n|subdivision_name1        = New York\n|subdivision_type2        = [[List of counties in New York|County]]\n|subdivision_name2        = [[Suffolk County, New York|Suffolk]]\n|government_footnotes     = \n|government_type          = \n|leader_title             = \n|leader_name              = \n|leader_title1            = \n|leader_name1             = \n|established_title        = \n|established_date         =\n\n<!-- Area -->\n|area_footnotes           = \n|